interestingcomments.content: That was the bigger problem for me with the M9. I was constantly battling magenta splotchiness in skin tones under artificial light. I was getting funky looking lips in all sorts of lighting conditions with my M9.

interestingcomments.content: You can only use the Philips 13139 75W bulb. If you're going to use another type the radius of the reflector is not OK which means a lot of light loss and the system can be overheated. If you can not get the right 75W Philips bulb anymore you have three options: - Osram HLX bulb 75W with an adapter for the reflector, which is made by Kienzle (Germany). - Heiland LED light source for V35 (Around Eur. 600,-) - Heiland LED light source with Split Grade (Around Eur. 1200,-)
